cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper deals with enhancing physical layer security in wireless communication channels, specifically in wiretap channels subject to Rician fading. This topic falls under the intersection of several computer science sub-disciplines, including information theory (cs.IT), cryptography (cs.CR), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), systems and control (cs.SY), and multimedia (cs.MM). However, given the focus on beamforming and channel fading, cs.IT and cs.CR are the most likely sub-categories. The paper's emphasis on location-based information and its application to wireless communication systems also suggests cs.NI as a likely sub-category. Finally, the use of multiple antennas and the optimization of beamforming solutions suggest cs.SY and cs.MM as possible sub-categories, respectively.
